messages.messageBody:
Oh Let Me, Let ME!!

I just found out what the secret handshake was myself, as I asked a few
days ago.
dd = darling daughter dh = dear husband ds = darling son, or some
variation of these. I was told they can also mean "something else" if you
are not feeling quite so affectionate towards one of your dearest family
members at the present moment. If you are fighting or something! ;-)

Consider yourself initiated! hehe

Nanci K. in Idaho

messages.messageBody:
<< Would someone please explain to me what these mean?
dh, dd, ds, and such. >>
Kelly,
dh= dear husband, dd= dear daughter, ds= dear son, mil= mother in law
sil=sister in law, lol= laughing out loud
Teresa

OR
dh(damn husband...)
AND
IMHO=in my humble opinion
rotflol=rolling on the floor laughing out loud
btw=by the way
etc
